      "side": 1,
      "message": "You should also add “unmapped” variants that ensure that you can issue a request to read unmapped memory and have it fail by returning false as opposed to, say, crashing. We will, from time to time, try to read memory that looks like it should be there but isn’t, and we don’t want that to take the handler down.\n\nThis may be easier to have an in-process-only test for. The Mach equivalent has TaskMemory.ReadSelfUnmapped and TaskMemory.ReadCStringSelfUnmapped.",
